<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-15T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-15T16:00:00-05:00" n="188" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">124.62/80: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-15T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 15,
                                        1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>9343. Department’s 9263.<note n="15" xml:id="d188fn15">Not
                                printed.</note></p>
                        <p>Since need for American Commissioner in Berlin is of extreme importance
                            Dresel should leave immediately on signature of protocol <pb facs="0331" n="246" xml:id="pg_246"/> by Germans and Department should be
                            informed of exact date of departure. If it appears to you wise
                            considering all circumstances for him to leave at an earlier date
                            explain facts to Department in order that proper instructions may be
                            cabled.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>